    <p>Consider the difference between a system that drafts an email for you and one that reads an inbound complaint, queries your CRM, issues a refund, and emails the customer without intervention. Think of agentic AI as the transition from a digital assistant that tells you the weather to a digital manager that autonomously reschedules your outdoor events and books an indoor venue. The infrastructure required to support these autonomous systems—such as advanced vector databases and low-latency compute—presents another compelling investment angle. As open-source models improve, the commoditization of base-level intelligence will force companies to differentiate on reliability, workflow integration, and domain-specific expertise. We are witnessing the birth of a new computing paradigm, one where software not only calculates but autonomously acts. The winners in this space will redefine the boundaries of what software can achieve, creating massive wealth for those who identify them early.</p>
