      <details>
        <summary>What are agentic AI stocks?</summary>
        <p>Agentic AI stocks are shares of companies that develop or deeply integrate autonomous artificial intelligence systems capable of taking independent actions to achieve specific goals, rather than just providing passive analytics.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How do agentic AI companies differ from traditional AI companies?</summary>
        <p>Traditional AI often focuses on pattern recognition and generating responses based on prompts (like LLMs). Agentic AI goes further by executing tasks, making decisions, and interacting with other systems autonomously to accomplish complex workflows.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>Are agentic AI stocks a good investment?</summary>
        <p>They represent a high-growth but potentially volatile sector. While the technology promises massive productivity gains and disruption across industries, investors must carefully evaluate individual companies' execution capabilities, valuations, and competitive moats.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>What sectors are most impacted by agentic AI?</summary>
        <p>Sectors such as enterprise software, cybersecurity, autonomous vehicles, robotics, and financial services are currently seeing the most significant impact from agentic AI implementation.</p>
      </details>

      <details>
        <summary>How can I identify genuine agentic AI stocks?</summary>
        <p>Look beyond the marketing hype. Evaluate if the company's AI solutions are actually executing tasks autonomously for clients, check their R&D spending, and look for tangible evidence of productivity improvements or cost reductions driven by their technology.</p>
